  MANILA, Philippines - Filipina boxer Nesthy Petecio marched into the round of 16 in the World Qualification Tournament for the Paris Olympics in Busto Arsizio, Italy, but four of her compatriots bowed out on Thursday, March 7.\", \"from\": 190, \"to\": 444, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 226, \"end\": 237, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\", \"score\": 0.9999921913677293, \"rank\": 7.645813886360405e-06, \"text\": \"Philippines\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\"}, {\"begin\": 255, \"end\": 269, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nesthy_Petecio\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nesthy Petecio\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nesthy_Petecio\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nesthy_Petecio\"}, {\"begin\": 363, \"end\": 376, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Busto_Arsizio\", \"score\": 0.999999990905053, \"rank\": 9.094690448933965e-09, \"text\": \"Busto Arsizio\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Busto_Arsizio\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Busto_Arsizio\"}, {\"begin\": 378, \"end\": 383, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9990130398836331, \"rank\": 0.0009590431174424412, \"text\": \"Italy\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Petecio nailed a unanimous decision victory over Romania's Maria Claudia Nechita in the women's 57kg class, serving as a bright spot on a rather unfortunate day for the Philippine boxing team.\", \"from\": 446, \"to\": 638, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 495, \"end\": 502, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romania_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9998590876167708, \"rank\": 0.00014041883180918876, \"text\": \"Romania\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romania_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romania_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Opening her campaign with afirst-round stoppageof Serbia's Andela Brankovic, Petecio floored Nechita with a vicious overhand right to the head earlier in the bout before she claimed the convincing 5-0 win.\", \"from\": 640, \"to\": 845, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 690, \"end\": 696, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9974722500513492, \"rank\": 0.002533780639487403, \"text\": \"Serbia\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 699, \"end\": 705, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andela\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Andela\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andela\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andela\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The judges scored it 30-26, 30-26, 30-26, 30-26, 29-27 in favor of Petecio.\", \"from\": 847, \"to\": 922, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"While Petecio advanced, John Marvin, Mark Ashley Fajardo, Ronald Chavez Jr., and Claudine Veloso all suffered exits as six of the 10 boxers the Association of Boxing Alliances in the Philippines sent to Italy got eliminated.\", \"from\": 924, \"to\": 1148, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 948, \"end\": 959, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Marvin_(boxer)\", \"score\": 0.6920628615771812, \"rank\": 0.4444444444445492, \"text\": \"John Marvin\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Marvin_(boxer)\", \"dbpedia